property.name: text
property.value: This example will run under Windows 64. This example contains 5 FMUs. One is a room model derived from the BESTEST, one is the shared wall between thermal zones, one is the first node of the radiant slab, one is the radiant slab, one is the last node of the radiant slab. The execution should be about 66s (no plots and JNA vs. 55 on JNI) using QSS2Fd and a tolerance of 1e-3. This model considers the full weather data which is an FMU for co-simulation 1.0.The controller is implemented in Java since the FMU controller seems to not be able to switch the controller on at the end of the simulation. The model which uses the FMU controller is OneLightCellWithFMUController. The room model has a window. The number of cores used for the simulation is two but there is no parallelism yet. The FMUs used for this simulation have been generated using Dymola 2015 FD01 Beta3. Older versions are generating wrong results when adding a window to the room model. Note: The nominal flow rate has been set to 1.5kg/s.
